## Third-Party Data Sources

This project displays data from the following public-domain sources. Their use
is subject to each agency's own terms:

- **NOAA / CPC** (National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, USA)
  Public domain — https://www.noaa.gov/information-technology/open-data-dissemination

- **NOAA PSL** (NOAA Physical Sciences Laboratory, USA) — IOD/DMI primary
  Public domain — https://psl.noaa.gov/data/correlation/dmi.data

- **JAMSTEC** (Japan Agency for Marine-Earth Science and Technology) — IOD/DMI fallback
  Public domain for research use — https://www.jamstec.go.jp/aplinfo/sintexf/iod/

- **CHIRPS v3** (Climate Hazards Group, UC Santa Barbara)
  Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0) — any use permitted with attribution
  https://chc.ucsb.edu/data/chirps3

- **India-WRIS** (India Water Resources Information System, CWC / NHP / World Bank)
  Open Government Data — https://indiawris.gov.in/

- **CWC Weekly Bulletin + data.gov.in** (Central Water Commission, Government of India)
  Open Government Data (OGD) Platform India — https://data.gov.in/

- **Observable Framework**
  ISC License — https://github.com/observablehq/framework/blob/main/LICENSE

No proprietary data, no personally identifiable information (PII), and no
protected health information (PHI) is stored, processed, or displayed by
this software.
